      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__can_1ga75aabbb82d96151cadfd3c26a2a285e9" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XCan_SetBaudRatePrescaler</definition>
        <argsstring>(XCan *InstancePtr, u8 Prescaler)</argsstring>
        <name>XCan_SetBaudRatePrescaler</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_can" kindref="compound">XCan</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u8</type>
          <declname>Prescaler</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This routine sets Baud Rate Prescaler value. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The system clock for the CAN controller is divided by (Prescaler + 1) to generate the quantum clock needed for sampling and synchronization. Read the device specification for details.</para><para>Baud Rate Prescaler could be set only after CAN device entered Configuration Mode. So please call <ref refid="group__can_1ga994a0b0bd9c938e99de9d7ffceb10ef3" kindref="member">XCan_EnterMode()</ref> to enter Configuration Mode before using this function.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_can" kindref="compound">XCan</ref> instance to be worked on. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Prescaler</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the value to set. Valid values are from 0 to 255.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if the Baud Rate Prescaler value is set successfully.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE if CAN device is not in Configuration Mode.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
